From: GeospatialDaryl <vandyke.geospatial@gmail.com>
Subject: arm64: dts: rockchip: rk3562-rk817-tablet-v10: Enable RKNPU

The rk3562.dtsi declares the NPU and its IOMMU with status "disabled"
and the tablet DTS never enables them, so the built image boots with
no /sys/class/devfreq/ff300000.npu and librknnrt cannot initialize.

The stock samwise vendor DTB (baseline/current-system/device-tree/fdt.dts
in rk3562deb) runs the NPU with status "okay", rknpu-supply pointing at
the vdd_npu PWM regulator, and the IOMMU enabled. Mirror that here,
matching the wiring rk3562-evb.dtsi uses. vdd_npu is already defined
(always-on pwm-regulator on pwm6) in this DTS.

---
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3562-rk817-tablet-v10.dts
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3562-rk817-tablet-v10.dts
@@ -934,6 +934,15 @@
 	status = "okay";
 };

+&rknpu {
+	rknpu-supply = <&vdd_npu>;
+	status = "okay";
+};
+
+&rknpu_mmu {
+	status = "okay";
+};
+
 &rkvdec {
 	status = "okay";
 };
